The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's call to pass a bill that addresses the immigration crisis in the United States. He emphasizes the need to secure the border and fulfill the duty to American citizens. President Trump is working with Congress to find a solution to reopen the government and secure the border. He proposes bipartisan legislation that would grant provisional status to current DACA and Temporary Protected Status (TPS) recipients. While this proposal would address the immediate security and humanitarian crisis at the southern border, it would not solve all immigration challenges.